OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry day for many with sunny
OL,6,Fspells, though the cloud may be thick
OL,7,Fenough to give the odd light shower,
OL,8,Fespecially during the morning. Feeling
OL,9,Fa little fresher than Monday.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FLargely dry overnight with a
OL,12,Fmix of cloud and clear spells. Turning
OL,13,Fchilly in any prolonged clear spells,
OL,14,Fwith perhaps some patchy mist and fog
OL,15,Fdeveloping.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FDry on Wednesday with a mix
OL,18,Fof cloud and sunny spells. Sunshine
OL,19,Ftending to increase throughout the
OL,20,Fafternoon, allowing it to feel warmer,
OL,21,Fespecially away from the south coast.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
